[3] Canada (Ontario)
Date: Tue 19 Jul 2022 4:12 PM ET
Source: CBC (Canadian Broadcasting Corporation) News, The Canadian Press report [edited]
https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/public-health-reports-230-monkeypox-cases-in-ontario-up-from-156-last-week-1.6525469


Public Health Ontario is reporting 230 confirmed cases of monkeypox in the province, most of which are located in Toronto. The tally as of Monday [17 Jul 2022] has risen by 74 cases from the 156 confirmed as of 11 Jul 2022.

The agency's latest report says the cases are largely in southern Ontario, with 172 cases in Toronto, as well as one each in Sudbury and North Bay. One of the confirmed cases is a female -- recorded last week [week of 11 Jul 2022] -- and the rest of the people affected are male, with an average age of 37.

Most cases are among men who report intimate contact with men but say anyone can get monkeypox. The report says 9 people have been hospitalized with the illness and one person has been in intensive care. There are also 8 probable monkeypox cases in Ontario, all in men between the ages of 31 and 69.

